LICENSE SCOPE EXPLANATION
==============

PERMITTED USES (No Additional Authorization Required):

1. Lawful Use
   Use only for lawful purposes in compliance with all applicable laws and regulations.

2. Content Creation
   Use the software to create content (videos, images, etc.) and commercialize it freely.

3. Personal/Internal Use
   Modify the software for yourself or your organization's internal use.

4. Open Source Distribution
   Distribute the software (including modified versions) under AGPL-3.0 terms.

5. Private Deployment
   Deploy the software for clients in private environments, provided that:
   - You retain all original copyright notices and attribution to "UseYing-Drama"
   - You do not misrepresent the software as your own creation
   - You do not remove or modify the original author information

==============
SPECIAL REQUIREMENTS FOR SaaS/ONLINE SERVICES
==============

Under AGPL v3.0, providing online services based on this software requires open-sourcing server-side modifications.

The following are considered SaaS/Online Services:
âœ“ Providing API services to third parties
âœ“ Embedding this software into other products/services offered to users
âœ“ Operating web-based services where users interact with the software over a network

The following are NOT considered SaaS/Online Services:
âœ— Private deployment for specific clients (as long as copyright notices remain intact)
âœ— Internal use within your organization
âœ— Creating and selling content made with the software

